            "value": "Hi,\nI use drawText(\u00e9) on my pc with xp it's work fine.\nI use on my serveur the same page it's doesn't work no letter with accentuation ar'ent print.\nMaybe It's look like this bug ZF-2387\nThank's, my soft works in production. \nBerty\n\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Pdf.php';\n$pdf = new Zend_Pdf();\n$font = Zend_Pdf_Font::fontWithName(Zend_Pdf_Font::FONT_HELVETICA_BOLD);\nforeach ($this->aff->GetIdListeInscrit() as $idsta){\n\t$inscrit=$this->aff->evaluation[$idsta];\n\t\t$pdf->pages[$idsta] = $pdf->newPage(Zend_Pdf_Page::SIZE_A4_LANDSCAPE););\n\t\t$pdf->pages[$idsta]->setFont($font, 13);\n\t\t$pdf->pages[$idsta]->drawText('\u00e9ae',\n\t\tmm2inch(34), mm2inch(83));\n\t}\n}\n\nheader(\"Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=\".$fichier);\n\t\t\theader(\"Expires: 0\");\n\t\t\theader(\"Content-type: application\/pdf\");\n\t\t\theader('Pragma: cache');\n\t\t\theader('Cache-control: private'); \/\/ IE BUG\necho $pdf->render();\n\n\n"
